    <p>An "accident" is an unanticipated, unintended event - a consequence of unforeseen factors. This is the very heart of people and institutions being able to successfully escape blame - it was an accident. When this implosion occurs it will not be an accident - it will be a result of culpable actions by culpable people and institutions. The question is whether or not they will escape the consequences by being able to claim"it was an accident". Yes I pointed the loaded gun at her. Yes I shouted "I'm going to kill you", but I didn't really mean it. I was upset. But then the gun just went off. I didn't mean to kill her. I don't know why it happened. I loved her. It was an accident.</p>

